external_knowledge:
- Average PSA and QED_Weighted are used to measure the "drug-likeness" of a molecule; 
- The higher the values, the more likely a molecule is to be a good drug candidate;
- Drug-likeness is an important factor in determining the potential effectiveness of a molecule as a drug.

sql:
SELECT molecule_id, psa
FROM molecules
WHERE psa > (SELECT AVG(psa) FROM molecules);

SELECT similarity_score
FROM molecule_similarity
WHERE molecule_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT molecule_id)
FROM access_logs
WHERE molecule_id IN (SELECT molecule_id FROM molecules WHERE mol_species = 1);

SELECT molecule_id
FROM molecule_properties
WHERE property_name = 'Molecular Formula';

SELECT molecule_id
FROM molecules
WHERE qed_weighted = (
  SELECT MAX(qed_weighted)
  FROM molecules
);
